title._content: Studio portrait of Captain McKilliam and two unidentified women

description._content:
This photo was probably taken in a London photographic studio. Text printed on the reverse includes: 'Lightning photography by the British automatic photography co., Ltd., 26-31 Eyre Street Hill, London, EC'. This photograph is part of the McKilliam family collection which includes material from several McKilliam family members. The majority of the collection relates to Captain Robert Basil Vincent McKilliam's working life as an apprentice, a mate, and then captain - much of which was with the Aberdeen White Star line.

The ANMM undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. 

Object no. ANMS0224[074]
